   9. Debugging in VS Code:
   - Outline the steps to set up and start debugging a simple program in VS Code. What are some key debugging features available in VS Code?
   
   To debug your program or code:

   - Set breakpoint to navigate the line of code whete you want to pause execution to inspect variable
   - Press "F5" to start debugging
   - Once the program hit the breakpoint. VS Code will swith to debug view showing debug-related ingo
   - You can hover over variables in the editor to see their current value
   - You can also use "Step Over", "Step Into", "Step Out" to navigate line by line and function.
   - click "continue" to resume execution
   - click 'stop' to teminate debugging session.

   Key Debugging Feature
   - Variable Watch: Monitor value of variable in real-time or when paseed at a breakpoint
   - Call Stack
   - Breakpoint: to pause execution at specific lines of code for inspection


   10. Using Source Control:
    - How can users integrate Git with VS Code for version control? Describe the process of initializing a repository, making commits, and pushing changes to GitHub.

    I usually use command line rater than the Source control UI

    Initializing a repo
    -Open integrated terminal
    enter "git init"
    create a repo on github
    then enter "git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name

    Making Commits
    - after making changes to file
    - enter "git status" to check the if the file has being modified
    - if yes, enter "git add filename" to register or approve modification
    - then to commit, enter "git commit -m Enter any message"

    To push changes
    - enter "git push -u origin branch_name"